episodes.title: The Falcon and the D'Ohman
episodes.plot: Homer tries to befriend the new security guard at the nuclear power plant, who for some unknown reason isn't interested and keeps having flashbacks to his violent past as a government agent.

episodes.title: Bart Stops to Smell the Roosevelts
episodes.plot: Superintendant Chalmers gets fired after using unconventional methods to teach Bart and his friends about Teddy Roosevelt, so the boys take over Springfield Elementary until he gets his old job back.

episodes.title: Treehouse of Horror XXII
episodes.plot: Homer takes a dangerous dive into an isolated canyon on Candy Peak, but when a crashing boulder traps his arm, he channels Aron Ralston to save himself. In "The Diving Bell and Butterball," the first of three hair-raising Halloween tales, a venomous spider bite leaves Homer paralyzed, but when Lisa discovers Homer's ability to communicate through natural gases, he is able to express his love for Marge. The killer spells continue in "Dial D for Diddly," when Ned Flanders, devout preacher by day, transforms into a cold-blooded vigilante by night. In the final terrifying...

episodes.title: Replaceable You
episodes.plot: Homer is betrayed by his new assistant at work and winds up working for her, and Bart and Martin create a science project that brings joy to the seniors at the Springfield Retirement Castle.

episodes.title: The Food Wife
episodes.plot: Homer is worried that he is no longer the cool parent after Marge, Bart, and Lisa become foodies.

episodes.title: The Book Job
episodes.plot: Homer and Bart put together a team to author the next successful tween novel franchise and make a million dollars, but discover that they need Lisa's help to pull it off.

episodes.title: The Man in the Blue Flannel Pants
episodes.plot: Homer gets promoted to accounts manager at the nuclear power plant, but soon learns the job robs you of your soul. Meanwhile, Lisa introduces Bart to "Little Women."

episodes.title: The Ten-Per-Cent Solution
episodes.plot: Krusty the Clown is stuck in a rut when the television network pulls his show from the air and his talent agency drops him as a client. But when the Simpsons introduce him to seasoned agent Annie, they are surprised to learn that Annie was Krusty's very first agent. Despite their rocky relationship, Annie is convinced to re-sign Krusty and craft his career comeback. But when Krusty's retro comedy show reboot is deemed a critical success, Krusty must decide to stay with his agent or side with the network executives.

episodes.title: Holidays of Future Passed
episodes.plot: Thirty years in the future the Simpsons get together for Christmas. Bart and Lisa are struggling as parents to connect with their children.

episodes.title: Politically Inept, with Homer Simpson
episodes.plot: Homer becomes the host of a popular political talk show, starts an "everyman" movement in Springfield, and ends up hand-picking Ted Nugent as the Republican nominee for president.

episodes.title: The D'oh-cial Network
episodes.plot: Lisa creates an online social network that becomes a Springfield obsession, but later becomes a victim of user backlash.

episodes.title: Moe Goes from Rags to Riches
episodes.plot: While Bart tries to regain Milhouse's friendship, Moe's bar cleaning rag tells his unlikely story of how he got to where he is today.

episodes.title: The Daughter Also Rises
episodes.plot: Lisa falls for an adventurous, Hemingway-esque young boy, while Bart and Millhouse set out to bust all the myths that surround Springfield Elementary School.

episodes.title: At Long Last Leave
episodes.plot: The town votes to kick the Simpsons out of Springfield, so they decide to move to the Outlands.

episodes.title: Exit Through the Kwik-E-Mart
episodes.plot: Bart becomes an urban vandal and decides to use Homer as his inspiration, while Apu hits hard times when a new trendy market takes all the Kwik-E-Mart customers.

episodes.title: How I Wet Your Mother
episodes.plot: The family break into Homer's dreams Inception-style after he begins wetting the bed.

episodes.title: Them, Robot
episodes.plot: Mr. Burns replaces all of the nuclear plant employees with robots--except for Homer, who stays along to supervise the robots and serve as a human scapegoat.

episodes.title: Beware My Cheating Bart
episodes.plot: Jimbo's girlfriend cheats on Jimbo with Bart, and Homer uses his new treadmill to catch up on a TV series about plane crash victims stranded on an island.

episodes.title: A Totally Fun Thing Bart Will Never Do Again
episodes.plot: Bart gets the family to take the cruise vacation of his dreams, and then launches a fiendish plot to ensure that it goes on forever.

episodes.title: The Spy Who Learned Me
episodes.plot: Homer uses his paid sick leave to improve his marriage, with the help of his imaginary friend, super-spy Stradivarius Cain. Meanwhile, Bart gets revenge on Nelson for stealing everyone's lunch money.

episodes.title: Ned 'N Edna's Blend Agenda
episodes.plot: After Ned and Edna announce publicly that they were secretly married, the two clash over how to raise Rod and Todd.

episodes.title: Lisa Goes Gaga
episodes.plot: After a desperate attempt by Lisa to become more popular backfires, Lady Gaga shows up in Springfield to help her with her self-esteem.
